==Dutch==

===Etymology===
From {{inh|nl|dum|sien}}, from {{inh|nl|odt|sian}}, from {{inh|nl|gmw-pro|*sehwan}}, from {{inh|nl|gem-pro|*sehwaną}}, from {{der|nl|ine-pro|*sekʷ-||to see, notice}}. 

Originally a class 5 strong verb, but the Germanic {{m|gem-pro||*h}} was lost from the infinitive and present tense forms through [[syncope]] in Old Dutch. However, it alternated with {{m|gem-pro||*g}} in the past tense through [[w:Grammatischer Wechsel|Grammatischer Wechsel]], and this remained.

